headline: 2 Reasons to Watch PH and 1 to Stay Cautious
summary: Parker-Hannifin trades at $525.48 per share and has stayed right on track with the overall market, losing 17% over the last six months while the S&P 500 is down 13.7%. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
